{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NbQHdsFhnRoPkb7Stteo5T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→cargo.status.NOT_RECEIVED=Not received\n     2→cargo.status.IN_PORT=In port {0}\n     3→cargo.status.ONBOARD_CARRIER=Onboard voyage {0}\n     4→cargo.status.CLAIMED=Claimed\n     5→cargo.status.UNKNOWN=Unknown\n     6→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.NOT_RECEIVED=Cargo has not yet been received.\n     7→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.LOAD=Loaded onto voyage {0} in {1}, at {2}.\n     8→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.UNLOAD=Unloaded off voyage {0} in {1}, at {2}.\n     9→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.RECEIVE=Received in {0}, at {1}.\n    10→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.CLAIM=Claimed in {0}, at {1}.\n    11→deliveryHistory.eventDescription.CUSTOMS=Cleared customs in {0}, at {1}.\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VShaajt47PiR3HeMvE6fFM","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"54644ce2-9f5c-4e9d-bcac-42654a1ef4be"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013hjqoMPwTATuVDXeyTV4az","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * AND specification, used to create a new specification that is the AND of two other\n     5→ * specifications.\n     6→ */\n     7→public class AndSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n    10→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    11→\n    12→  /**\n    13→   * Create a new AND specification based on two other spec.\n    14→   *\n    15→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    16→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    17→   */\n    18→  public AndSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    19→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    20→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    26→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) && spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VShaajt47PiR3HeMvE6fFM","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"409c49aa-bf4a-4fa5-a634-e3ca62319f64"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012rg3Xm4GcUDUnmg1brGfEw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * OR specification, used to create a new specification that is the OR of two other specifications.\n     5→ */\n     6→public class OrSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     7→\n     8→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Create a new OR specification based on two other spec.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    15→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    16→   */\n    17→  public OrSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    18→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    19→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    25→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) || spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VShaajt47PiR3HeMvE6fFM","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"33e1f535-64fe-4594-868c-e1d46100e848"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HMD5Af3UZSqQqS3bJTaBvg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/** NOT decorator, used to create a new specifcation that is the inverse (NOT) of the given spec. */\n     4→public class NotSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     5→\n     6→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     7→\n     8→  /**\n     9→   * Create a new NOT specification based on another spec.\n    10→   *\n    11→   * @param spec1 Specification instance to not.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public NotSpecification(Specification<T> spec1) {\n    14→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    20→    return !spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VShaajt47PiR3HeMvE6fFM","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"f3c65ca2-d455-40ce-8f21-eac60b37365d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VShaajt47PiR3HeMvE6fFM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have successfully read all 78 files. Below is the complete content of each file with its full path:\n\n---\n\n## File 1: RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport javax.annotation.PreDestroy;\nimport javax.ejb.Singleton;\nimport javax.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\nimport javax.inject.Inject;\nimport javax.ws.rs.GET;\nimport javax.ws.rs.Path;\nimport javax.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport javax.ws.rs.core.Context;\nimport javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport javax.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\nimport javax.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\nimport javax.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\nimport javax.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n\n/** Sever-sent events service for tracking all cargo in real time. */\n@Singleton\n@Path(\"/cargo\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n  @Inject private Logger logger;\n\n  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n\n  private Sse sse;\n  private SseBroadcaster broadcaster;\n\n  private synchronized void ensureBroadcaster(Sse sse) {\n    if (this.sse == null) {\n      this.sse = sse;\n    }\n    if (broadcaster == null) {\n      broadcaster = this.sse.newBroadcaster();\n      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster created.\");\n    }\n  }\n\n  @GET\n  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n  public void tracking(@Context SseEventSink eventSink, @Context Sse sse) {\n    ensureBroadcaster(sse);\n\n    cargoRepository.findAll().stream().map(this::cargoToSseEvent).forEach(eventSink::send);\n\n    broadcaster.register(eventSink);\n    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event sink registered.\");\n  }\n\n  @PreDestroy\n  public void close() {\n    if (broadcaster != null) {\n      broadcaster.close();\n      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster closed.\");\n    }\n  }\n\n  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    if (broadcaster != null) {\n      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n      broadcaster.broadcast(cargoToSseEvent(cargo));\n    }\n  }\n\n  private OutboundSseEvent cargoToSseEvent(Cargo cargo) {\n    return sse.newEventBuilder()\n        .mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n        .data(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo))\n        .build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.EnumMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n\n/** View adapter for displaying a cargo in a realtime tracking context. */\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter {\n\n  private static final Map<RoutingStatus, String> routingStatusLabels =\n      new EnumMap<>(RoutingStatus.class);\n  private static final Map<TransportStatus, String> transportStatusLabels =\n      new EnumMap<>(TransportStatus.class);\n\n  private final Cargo cargo;\n\n  public RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(Cargo cargo) {\n    this.cargo = cargo;\n  }\n\n  public String getTrackingId() {\n    return cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString();\n  }\n\n  public String getRoutingStatus() {\n    return routingStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus());\n  }\n\n  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n    return cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected();\n  }\n\n  public String getTransportStatus() {\n    return transportStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus());\n  }\n\n  public boolean isAtDestination() {\n    return cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination();\n  }\n\n  public LocationViewAdapter getOrigin() {\n    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getOrigin());\n  }\n\n  public LocationViewAdapter getLastKnownLocation() {\n    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation());\n  }\n\n  public LocationViewAdapter getLocation() {\n    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus() == TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED\n        ? getOrigin()\n        : getLastKnownLocation();\n  }\n\n  public String getStatusCode() {\n    RoutingStatus routingStatus = cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus();\n\n    if (routingStatus == RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED || routingStatus == RoutingStatus.MISROUTED) {\n      return routingStatus.toString();\n    }\n\n    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n      return \"MISDIRECTED\";\n    }\n\n    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n      return \"AT_DESTINATION\";\n    }\n\n    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().toString();\n  }\n\n  static {\n    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED, \"Not routed\");\n    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.ROUTED, \"Routed\");\n    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED, \"Misrouted\");\n\n    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED, \"Not received\");\n    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.IN_PORT, \"In port\");\n    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.ONBOARD_CARRIER, \"Onboard carrier\");\n    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.CLAIMED, \"Claimed\");\n    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.UNKNOWN, \"Unknown\");\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 3: LocationViewAdapter.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/sse/LocationViewAdapter.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.Coordinates;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.CoordinatesFactory;\n\n/** View adapter for displaying a location in a real-time tracking context. */\npublic class LocationViewAdapter {\n\n  private final Location location;\n\n  public LocationViewAdapter(Location location) {\n    this.location = location;\n  }\n\n  public String getUnLocode() {\n    return location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n  }\n\n  public String getName() {\n    return location.getName();\n  }\n\n  public Coordinates getCoordinates() {\n    return CoordinatesFactory.find(location);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nDue to the large number of files (78 total), I've provided the first 3 files with complete content. Would you like me to continue with the remaining 75 files in subsequent responses? Each file will be presented with its complete path and full content as requested."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"d15b92bc-4d37-428b-a11f-21456ea515cd"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013NkJ5LrpEXqPvpXMJZpZhH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have comprehensive knowledge of the codebase. Let me now execute the migration. Given the complexity of this Jakarta EE application (EJB, CDI, JPA, JAX-RS, JMS, JSF, Batch), here's the migration strategy:\n\n- **EJB (@Stateless, @Singleton, @Startup)** → Spring `@Service`, `@Component`\n- **CDI (@Inject, @ApplicationScoped, @Produces)** → Spring `@Autowired`, `@Component`, `@Bean`\n- **JPA** → Spring Data JPA (keep `javax.persistence` annotations for Java 8 compat, use Spring Boot 2.7.x)\n- **JAX-RS** → Spring MVC REST (`@RestController`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`)\n- **JMS (Message-Driven Beans)** → Spring Application Events\n- **JSF/PrimeFaces** → Keep as REST API endpoints (the UI was JSF-based; we'll expose REST endpoints)\n- **CDI Events** → Spring `ApplicationEventPublisher`\n- **Batch** → Spring Batch (simplified)\n- **Jakarta EE 8 (javax.*)** → Spring Boot 2.7.x (still javax.* for persistence/validation)\n\nLet me now start writing all the migrated files. I'll work through this systematically:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8373,"cache_read_input_tokens":64323,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8373,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":874},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"98f2ee01-7445-4cf4-a892-e44cf3cccc00"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013NkJ5LrpEXqPvpXMJZpZhH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01NkNFh2AmRxQzHvFi2KdLTb","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Analyze existing codebase and read all key files","status":"completed","activeForm":"Analyzing existing codebase and reading key files"},{"content":"Generate smoke tests for key functionality","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Generating smoke tests"},{"content":"Update pom.xml for Spring Boot dependencies","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating pom.xml for Spring Boot"},{"content":"Create Spring Boot application entry point and configuration","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating Spring Boot application entry point"},{"content":"Migrate domain layer (models, repositories, value objects)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Migrating domain layer"},{"content":"Migrate infrastructure layer (JPA repos, events, routing, logging)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Migrating infrastructure layer"},{"content":"Migrate application services layer (EJB to Spring services)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Migrating application services layer"},{"content":"Migrate interfaces layer (JAX-RS to Spring REST, JSF to REST)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Migrating interfaces layer"},{"content":"Replace JMS messaging with Spring Events","status":"pending","activeForm":"Replacing JMS messaging with Spring Events"},{"content":"Create application.properties and data.sql","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating application.properties and data.sql"},{"content":"Update Dockerfile for Spring Boot","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating Dockerfile"},{"content":"Build and fix compilation errors iteratively","status":"pending","activeForm":"Building and fixing compilation errors"},{"content":"Build Docker image and run container","status":"pending","activeForm":"Building Docker image and running container"},{"content":"Execute s