{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KXjv1b8ECRLEAUC5BSHwpL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→/** Uniquely identifies a particular cargo. Automatically generated by the application. */\n    10→@Embeddable\n    11→public class TrackingId implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Column(name = \"tracking_id\", unique = true, updatable = false)\n    16→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Tracking ID cannot be empty.\")\n    17→  private String id;\n    18→\n    19→  public TrackingId() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public TrackingId(String id) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(id);\n    23→    this.id = id;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  public String getIdString() {\n    27→    return id;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    32→    if (this == o) {\n    33→      return true;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof TrackingId)) {\n    37→      return false;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    TrackingId other = (TrackingId) o;\n    41→\n    42→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public int hashCode() {\n    47→    return id.hashCode();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  boolean sameValueAs(TrackingId other) {\n    51→    return other != null && this.id.equals(other.id);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public String toString() {\n    56→    return id;\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"491f00c2-5fe8-4edf-983a-3ddb3d6b5d68"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P4waUhjRNrntFyAayR25q4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→public enum TransportStatus {\n     4→  NOT_RECEIVED,\n     5→  IN_PORT,\n     6→  ONBOARD_CARRIER,\n     7→  CLAIMED,\n     8→  UNKNOWN;\n     9→\n    10→  public boolean sameValueAs(TransportStatus other) {\n    11→    return this.equals(other);\n    12→  }\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"d582f04d-4cde-42bd-93a5-b74ca6d5f0de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHiTjyUWs4PTjxkKt1NAd7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→public enum RoutingStatus {\n     4→  NOT_ROUTED,\n     5→  ROUTED,\n     6→  MISROUTED;\n     7→\n     8→  public boolean sameValueAs(RoutingStatus other) {\n     9→    return this.equals(other);\n    10→  }\n    11→}\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"57be7c5a-7d55-4ba1-a34f-c95cf443222b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EwBqcLXqUeMMbLZLVDMqQg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class HandlingEventFactory implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    23→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    24→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    25→\n    26→  /**\n    27→   * @param registrationTime time when this event was received by the system\n    28→   * @param completionTime when the event was completed, for example finished loading\n    29→   * @param trackingId cargo tracking id\n    30→   * @param voyageNumber voyage number\n    31→   * @param unlocode United Nations Location Code for the location of the event\n    32→   * @param type type of event\n    33→   * @return A handling event.\n    34→   * @throws UnknownVoyageException if there's no voyage with this number\n    35→   * @throws UnknownCargoException if there's no cargo with this tracking id\n    36→   * @throws UnknownLocationException if there's no location with this UN Locode\n    37→   */\n    38→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look at the exception handling more seriously.\n    39→  public HandlingEvent createHandlingEvent(\n    40→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    41→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    42→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    43→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    44→      UnLocode unlocode,\n    45→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    46→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    47→    Cargo cargo = findCargo(trackingId);\n    48→    Voyage voyage = findVoyage(voyageNumber);\n    49→    Location location = findLocation(unlocode);\n    50→\n    51→    try {\n    52→      if (voyage == null) {\n    53→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location);\n    54→      } else {\n    55→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location, voyage);\n    56→      }\n    57→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    58→      throw new CannotCreateHandlingEventException(e);\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  private Cargo findCargo(TrackingId trackingId) throws UnknownCargoException {\n    63→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    64→\n    65→    if (cargo == null) {\n    66→      throw new UnknownCargoException(trackingId);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    return cargo;\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  private Voyage findVoyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) throws UnknownVoyageException {\n    73→    if (voyageNumber == null) {\n    74→      return null;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    78→\n    79→    if (voyage == null) {\n    80→      throw new UnknownVoyageException(voyageNumber);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return voyage;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private Location findLocation(UnLocode unlocode) throws UnknownLocationException {\n    87→    Location location = locationRepository.find(unlocode);\n    88→\n    89→    if (location == null) {\n    90→      throw new UnknownLocationException(unlocode);\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    return location;\n    94→  }\n    95→}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"4c4658dc-3f14-4416-b9ea-825d094eb414"}
