{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LFKbp19m97NFABhvyBDYcF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     4→public class DomainObjectUtils {\n     5→\n     6→  /** Prevent instantiation. */\n     7→  private DomainObjectUtils() {}\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param actual actual value\n    11→   * @param safe a null-safe value\n    12→   * @param <T> type\n    13→   * @return actual value, if it's not null, or safe value if the actual value is null.\n    14→   */\n    15→  public static <T> T nullSafe(T actual, T safe) {\n    16→    return actual == null ? safe : actual;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"ed304023-95e2-4e7a-8ecc-d5a2b4e4b611"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MPHC5RQQh3952RfUpnfzuG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Abstract base implementation of composite {@link Specification} with default implementations for\n     5→ * {@code and}, {@code or} and {@code not}.\n     6→ */\n     7→public abstract class AbstractSpecification<T> implements Specification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public abstract boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    12→\n    13→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification) {\n    16→    return new AndSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification) {\n    22→    return new OrSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification) {\n    28→    return new NotSpecification<>(specification);\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"787b7a24-2d2e-4ade-91a6-0ea695e4f63e"}
