{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WEK4wM3YRbR63Srf398MzT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All the domain layer files have been successfully migrated. Let me create a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI have successfully migrated the Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker domain layer to Spring Boot 2.7.x. Here's what was done:\n\n### Files Modified for Spring Migration:\n\n1. **HandlingEventFactory.java** - Migrated from Jakarta CDI to Spring:\n   - Changed `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n   - Changed `@Inject` to `@Autowired`\n   - Removed `Serializable` interface and `serialVersionUID`\n\n2. **Repository Interfaces** - Converted to clean Spring-compatible interfaces:\n   - `CargoRepository.java`\n   - `LocationRepository.java`\n   - `VoyageRepository.java`\n   - `HandlingEventRepository.java`\n   - `RoutingService.java`\n\n### Files Kept Unchanged (Compatible with Spring Boot 2.7.x):\n\nAll JPA entities and value objects were preserved unchanged because Spring Boot 2.7.x still uses `javax.persistence.*` and `javax.validation.*`:\n\n**Cargo Domain:**\n- Cargo.java, TrackingId.java, Delivery.java, Itinerary.java, Leg.java\n- RouteSpecification.java, HandlingActivity.java\n- TransportStatus.java (enum), RoutingStatus.java (enum)\n\n**Handling Domain:**\n- HandlingEvent.java, HandlingHistory.java\n- CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java\n- UnknownCargoException.java, UnknownLocationException.java, UnknownVoyageException.java\n\n**Location Domain:**\n- Location.java, UnLocode.java, SampleLocations.java\n\n**Voyage Domain:**\n- Voyage.java, VoyageNumber.java, Schedule.java, CarrierMovement.java, SampleVoyages.java\n\n**Shared Domain:**\n- DomainObjectUtils.java, Specification.java, AbstractSpecification.java\n- AndSpecification.java, OrSpecification.java, NotSpecification.java\n\n### Key Migration Principles Applied:\n\n1. ✅ Kept `javax.persistence.*` annotations (Spring Boot 2.7.x compatible)\n2. ✅ Kept `javax.validation.*` annotations (Spring Boot 2.7.x compatible)\n3. ✅ Replaced `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Component`\n4. ✅ Replaced `@Inject` with `@Autowired`\n5. ✅ Repository interfaces remain as plain Java interfaces (no annotations needed)\n6. ✅ All JPA entities retain `Serializable` and `serialVersionUID` (required for JPA)\n7. ✅ Exception classes kept `@ApplicationException` annotation (from javax.ejb, will need handling at service layer)\n\nAll files have been successfully written to the output directory and are ready for the Spring Boot migration!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08d2657a-d0d7-410a-941f-d00e90a603b3","uuid":"4233b088-0bcf-4bdf-a312-c0fb50f03348"}
